    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for judges to push a conservative agenda by picking and choosing historical facts that fit what they want to do. how do scholars respond to that critique? like, is there a legitimate way to do it without it just being political?",
