    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but some people argue that even if you try to be objective, the history itself is pretty biased and doesn't account for modern values like equality or privacy in the way we need them now. so instead of being \"objective,\" isn't it more like they're just using a dead person's worldview to justify current laws? isn't that just a form of judicial activism in itself?",
